Looks like the InterWiki links at MediaWiki don't work anymore.

https://www.mediawiki.org/w/api.php?action=query&meta=siteinfo&siprop=interwikimap

We'll need to

# Notify MediaWiki that the InterWiki prefix is now ##https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/##
# Add redirects to support the old link format of ##http://www.emacswiki.org/cgi-bin/wiki.pl?##

-- AaronHawley

[new:AlexSchroeder:2016-11-23 11:40 UTC]
No, we actually have tons of redirects for old URLs and this one just slipped through the cracks.
I've fixed it, hopefully. :)

The relevant nginx config:

{{{
rewrite "^/(?:cgi-bin/)?(?:emacs(?:-[a-z][a-z])+|emacs\.pl|wiki|wiki\.pl)/(.*)" "/emacs/$1" permanent;
rewrite "^/cgi-bin/wiki.pl"     "/emacs" permanent; # https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/2016-11-22
rewrite "^/cgi-bin/emacs/(.*)"  "/emacs/$1" permanent;
}}}

Test:

* http://www.emacswiki.org/cgi-bin/wiki.pl?2016-11-22

Thanks for reporting little details such as this one!

-- [[Alex Schroeder]]
